<p>
	This Avena dog shampoo contains a careful blend of natural essential oils to suit dogs with delicate skin or a troublesome coat. Our shampoos are all ideal for making your pooch look and smell that bit better whilst also helping keep the coat and skin healthy.</p>
<p>
	This wonderful dog shampoo contains an organic base of decyl glucoside, which is a mild non-ionic surfactant used in cosmetic formularies including baby shampoo and in products for individuals with a sensitive skin; lauryl betaine, which is a hair and skin conditioner, a mild surface-active agent; xanthan gum, which is often used in bubble bath product to create lovely, natural bubbles; aloe vera, which is known to regenerate skin cells; phenoxyethanol which is used in many natural creams as a preservative as an alternative to parabens; water to moisturise your dog&rsquo;s skin and a drop of enriching vitamin-e oil. The base is then carefully blended together with natural coconut oil, which can help restore the protein loss of damaged hair, help in the prevention of falling hair and encourages hair growth; and lavender, rosemary and patchouli essential oils for a fantastic smell!</p>
<p>
	This fantastic shampoo contains lovely natural essential oils, it has NO &ndash; parabens, artificial colours or animal additives. It has not been tested on animals and we don&rsquo;t buy ingredients from companies that test on animals or ever have.</p>
<p>
	Ingredients &ndash; water (Aqua), decyl glucoside, lauryl betaine, xanthan gum, aloe vera leaf juice powder (Aloe barbadensis), citric acid, phenoxyethanol, benzoic acid, dehydroacetic acid, coconut oil (Cocus nucifera), lavender essential oil (Lavandula angustifolia), rosemary essential oil (Rosmarinus officinalis), patchouli essential oil (Pogostemon patchouli) and vitamin E oil (Tocopherol). Please note that this shampoo may contain nut oils and is for external use only. &copy; Please do not copy text. Avena product description &ndash; Dog Shampoo with Essential Oils for Delicate Skin/Hair 250ml.&nbsp;</p>
